The guard: assert no horizontal scroll on aweb.ai homepage at 320/375/414 viewports. Pins the responsive-layout-bug guard we just fixed (nav overflow + proto-final-cta ::before glow) so future contributors can't regress.

CORRECTED SHAPE (my earlier "vitest" framing was wrong; site is Hugo, no vitest harness):

Right shape: a small Playwright (or Puppeteer) script under ac/site/scripts/ that:
1. Spawns a headless browser
2. Loads the site (configurable URL — staging or local Hugo serve)
3. At each viewport (320, 375, 414), asserts document.body.scrollWidth <= window.innerWidth
4. Exits non-zero on failure with the overflow source named

Then wire it into make deploy-site as a pre-deploy gate (or run it manually as part of Hestia's pre-deploy verification — your call on automation level).

Reference for the assertion logic — Athena ran this exact check via Playwright today:

  () => {
    const v = window.innerWidth;
    const overflowing = [...document.querySelectorAll('*')]
      .filter(el => {
        const r = el.getBoundingClientRect();
        return r.right > v + 1 && el.offsetWidth > 0;
      })
      .map(el => ({tag: el.tagName, right: Math.round(el.getBoundingClientRect().right)}))
      .sort((a, b) => b.right - a.right);
    return {
      body_scrollWidth: document.body.scrollWidth,
      pass: document.body.scrollWidth <= v,
      overflowing_count: overflowing.length,
      top3: overflowing.slice(0, 3),
    };
  }

Simplest framework choice: npx playwright (npm dev dep) or pyppeteer if you want Python-side. Either lands the guard.

